FL,464,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F463A1776874271
OL,3,CAlmost half of people living with MS
OL,4,Cchallenged for using accessible
OL,5,Cfacilities
OL,7,FOver 6,000 people in Wales live with
OL,8,FMS. It's a condition that affects the
OL,9,Fbrain and spinal cord, impacting how
OL,10,Fyou move, think and feel. But symptoms
OL,11,Fcan often be invisible.
OL,13,FAlmost a third of those surveyed said
OL,14,Fthat fear of judgement stopped them
OL,15,Ffrom leaving the house, and 57% said
OL,16,Fthey avoided using accessible
OL,17,Ffacilities because of this.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G5/7
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,464,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F463A1776874271
OL,3,CAlmost half of people living with MS
OL,4,Cchallenged for using accessible
OL,5,Cfacilities
OL,7,F"It's really shocking. It's shocking
OL,8,Fthat people are experiencing this,"
OL,9,Fsaid Shelley Elgin, Director of the MS
OL,10,FSociety in Wales.
OL,12,F"The survey showed us that people are
OL,13,Fafraid to leave their own home for
OL,14,Ffear of judgement and that is really
OL,15,Fworrying for people living with MS.
OL,26,@oD@AOUpD@cO]tD@AOU
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G6/7
